The paper deals with the computational complexity of optimal alignment of diploid sequences, which involves finding the best alignment of two related sequences. This problem is related to graph theory and combinatorial optimization, which are central topics in computer science. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), followed by cs.CG (Computational Geometry), cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics), cs.CC (Computational Complexity), and cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
